# Radix UI

When building interactive or accessible UI, **use a Radix primitive if one fits the job**. Do not hand-roll modals, menus, toasts, tooltips, selects, switches, accordions, or similar behavior when `@radix-ui/react-*` already covers it.

Style with Tailwind and project semantic tokens (`dark-mode-ui.mdc`). Wrap primitives in atoms/molecules (`atomic-components.mdc`) — do not import Radix directly in `src/app/` routes or organisms.

## Required workflow

1. Check whether a [Radix Primitive](https://www.radix-ui.com/primitives/docs/overview/getting-started) matches the interaction (dialog, toast, select, dropdown, tabs, tooltip, popover, accordion, collapsible, checkbox, switch, radio, slider, scroll area, etc.)
2. Prefer an existing project wrapper under `src/components/` if one already exists
3. If none exists, install the matching package and create the atom/molecule wrapper first
4. Only use a custom DOM + hooks implementation when no Radix primitive is suitable

```bash
# Install only the primitives you need
yarn add @radix-ui/react-toast
```

## Existing wrappers (non-exhaustive)

| Primitive | Package | Typical wrapper |
|-----------|---------|-----------------|
| Labels | `@radix-ui/react-label` | `FormField`, `atoms/Label` |
| Checkbox / Switch | `@radix-ui/react-checkbox`, `@radix-ui/react-switch` | `atoms/Checkbox`, `atoms/Switch` |
| Select | `@radix-ui/react-select` | `atoms/Select` or `molecules/SelectField` |
| Radio group | `@radix-ui/react-radio-group` | `molecules/RadioGroupField` |
| Dialog / Alert dialog | `@radix-ui/react-dialog`, `@radix-ui/react-alert-dialog` | `molecules/Modal`, `molecules/ConfirmDialog` |
| Dropdown menu | `@radix-ui/react-dropdown-menu` | `molecules/DropdownMenu` |
| Tabs | `@radix-ui/react-tabs` | `molecules/Tabs` |
| Tooltip | `@radix-ui/react-tooltip` | `atoms/Tooltip` |
| Popover | `@radix-ui/react-popover` | `molecules/Popover` |
| Accordion | `@radix-ui/react-accordion` | `molecules/Accordion` |
| Collapsible | `@radix-ui/react-collapsible` | `atoms/Collapsible` |
| Toast | `@radix-ui/react-toast` | `atoms/Toast` |

This table is a map of what is already wrapped — **not** a closed list. New suitable primitives should still be used and wrapped the same way.

## Forms

- Pair Radix **Label** (or **FormField**) with native `input` / `textarea` or Radix **Select** / **Checkbox**
- Every control needs a stable `id`, matching `htmlFor`, and `name` for `FormData`
- Keep submission on Server Actions (`server-actions.mdc`) — Radix handles a11y, not transport

```js
// ✅ GOOD — Radix label + native input, submitted via action
import * as Label from "@radix-ui/react-label";

<Label.Root htmlFor="email">Email</Label.Root>
<input id="email" name="email" type="email" required />
```

```js
// ❌ BAD — custom toast/modal/menu when Radix already provides one
<div role="status">No users matched…</div>
```

```js
// ✅ GOOD — wrap Radix and reuse the atom
import Toast from "@/components/atoms/Toast/Toast";
<Toast message="No users matched…" duration={5000} />
```

## Avoid

- Custom accessible behavior for patterns Radix already covers
- Third-party UI kits (MUI, Chakra, Headless UI) for the same jobs
- Inline Radix imports in `src/app/` — always wrap in `src/components/`
- Installing alternate libraries for toasts, dialogs, selects, etc. when Radix fits
